olive oil
drizzle white wine vinegar
3 Potato
1 sprig Spring Onion
1 Carrot
1 packet Diced Bacon
1 packet Plant-Based Mince
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet BBQ Sauce
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into fries.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice spring onion. Grate carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Add diced bacon and cook, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 6-7 minutes. Transfer to a small bowl.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook veggie mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add All-American spice blend and cook, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove pan from heat, then add baby leaves, BBQ sauce and a splash of water. Stir until wilted.
• Add shredded Cheddar cheese to the pan and cover with a lid (or foil) so it melts.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, carrot, mayonnaise and a drizzle of white wine vinegar. Season to taste.

• Divide potato fries between plates.
• Top with cheesy plant-based mince and sprinkle over bacon.
• Garnish with spring onion. Serve with creamy slaw. Enjoy!